Mayan chacmool sculptures such as this one heavily influenced which of the following twentieth-century sculptors? <image 1>

A. Louise Bourgeois
B. Henry Moore
C. Barbara Hepworth
D. Constantin Brancusi

The Mayan chacmool sculptures, which are known for their reclining figures, have been influential in the work of several artists. Among the options provided, Constantin Brancusi is known to have been particularly influenced by ancient art forms, including those from Mesoamerica. Therefore, the correct answer is:

D. Constantin Brancusi
